    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Logging &amp; Diagnostics</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">EmulatR&apos;s diagnostics are driven by runtime <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_*</text> trace gates and a built-in retire profiler. Most output goes to the process&apos;s standard error, so a run is captured by redirecting stderr to a log (<text styleclass="Code Example">2&gt; run.log</text>).</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">In this section</para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="NotesBox" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Diagnostics &amp; Debugging -- the trace gates, probe / break gates, and the compile-time diagnostics.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">SRM Performance Logging -- where profiling output is written.</li>
